<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-30-1037 </DOCNO><TEXT>Both commitment of the public to the issues and commitment to public involvementby policy makers are discussed. In implementing the Low Level RadioactiveWaste Policy Act, the use of the following techniques have proved effectivein some siting cases: balanced advisory committees, economic incentivepackages, assistance to communities, impact assistance, role for localgovernment in oversight of operations, and education. Observations aremade about two regulatory issues: the exemption of same radioactive wastestreams from disposal in waste facilities because they are consideredBelow Regulatory Concern and export/import restrictions between regionalCompact boundaries.</TEXT></DOC>